ARCOMMANDS_Filter.h File Reference

libARCommands filter header. This file contains all declarations needed to create and use a commands filter More...

Detailed Description

libARCommands filter header. This file contains all declarations needed to create and use a commands filter

Note
Autogenerated file

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum eARCOMMANDS_FILTER_ERROR

Error code for ARCOMMANDS_Filter functions.

Enumerator
ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_OK 

No error.

ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_ERROR_ALLOC 

Memory allocation error.

ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_ERROR_BAD_STATUS 

The given status is not a valid status.

ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_ERROR_BAD_FILTER 

The given filter is not a valid filter.

ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_ERROR_BAD_BUFFER 

The given buffer is not a valid buffer.

ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_ERROR_OTHER 

Any other error.

enum eARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS

Status code for ARCOMMANDS_Filter_FilterCommand function.

Enumerator
ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS_ALLOWED 

The command should pass the filter.

ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS_BLOCKED 

The command should not pass the filter.

ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS_UNKNOWN 

Unknown command. The command was possibly added in a newer version of libARCommands, or is an invalid command.

ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS_ERROR 

The filtering of the command failed.

Function Documentation

void ARCOMMANDS_Filter_DeleteFilter ( ARCOMMANDS_Filter_t **  filter)

Deletes an ARCOMMANDS_Filter_t.

Parameters
filterThe filter to delete.
eARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS ARCOMMANDS_Filter_FilterCommand ( ARCOMMANDS_Filter_t *  filter,
uint8_t *  buffer,
uint32_t  len,
eARCOMMANDS_FILTER_ERROR *  error 
)

Filter an ARCommand.

Parameters
filterThe ARCOMMANDS_Filter_t to use for filtering.
bufferThe ARCommand buffer.
lenThe ARCommand buffer length.
errorOptionnal pointer which will hold the error code.
Returns
An eARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS status code
ARCOMMANDS_Filter_t* ARCOMMANDS_Filter_NewFilter ( eARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS  defaultBehavior,
eARCOMMANDS_FILTER_ERROR *  error 
)

Creates a new ARCOMMANDS_Filter_t.

Parameters
defaultBehaviorThe default behavior of the filter (must be either ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS_BLOCKED or ARCOMMANDS_FILTER_STATUS_ALLOWED).
errorOptionnal pointer which will hold the error code.
Warning
This function allocates memory.
Note
The memory must be freed by a call to ARCOMMANDS_Filter_DeleteFilter.
Returns
A new ARCOMMANDS_Filter_t instance. NULL in case of error.
